 Celtic striker John Guidetti has won the Scottish Professional Football League player of the month award for October.

The on-loan Manchester City striker hit two goals in three Scottish Premiership games last month and also netted a hat-trick in a League Cup win over Partick Thistle.

The 22-year-old Swede has scored nine goals in nine games since joining the club.

